target: enclosures
validations:
  - name: place_enclosure
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the player can place an enclosure on the map. Selecting
        a biome from the build menu and clicking on open grass tiles should
        create an enclosure at that location. The enclosure should appear as
        a colored rectangle matching the biome. The player's money should
        decrease by the biome's base cost. The tiles under the enclosure
        should become occupied and reject further building.
  - name: condition_degrades
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that enclosure condition degrades over time. After placing an
        enclosure and waiting, its condition value should decrease from the
        starting value of 100. Selecting the enclosure should show its
        current condition in the info panel. The condition should decline
        gradually, not jump suddenly.
  - name: repair_and_upgrade
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the player can repair and upgrade enclosures. Selecting
        a degraded enclosure and clicking a repair button should restore its
        condition to 100 and deduct the repair cost from the player's
        money. An upgrade button should increase the enclosure's capacity
        and deduct the upgrade cost. Both operations should be reflected
        in the enclosure's info panel.
